com.github.yeetmanlord.reflection_api

Class NMSObjectReflection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.yeetmanlord.reflection_api.NMSObjectReflection
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NMSAxisAlignedBBReflection, NMSBlockPositionReflection, NMSChatComponentTextReflection, NMSDataWatcherReflection, NMSEntityReflection, NMSNBTTagCompoundReflection, NMSNetworkManagerReflection, NMSPacketReflection, NMSPlayerConnectionReflection, NMSPlayerInteractManagerReflection, NMSScoreboardTeamReflection, NMSServerReflection, NMSVec3DReflection, NMSWorldServerReflection

    public class NMSObjectReflection
extends java.lang.Object
    Implementation Note
    If you were to ever extend this class and create mappings for it, I recommend following this rule:
      You should have a public static field called `staticClass` which is the NMS class that object refers to. This is for mappings testing.
      In general, it's also good practice since it makes code more concise.

      • invokeMethodForNmsObject

        public java.lang.Object invokeMethodForNmsObject(java.lang.String methodName,
                                                 @Nonnull
                                                 java.lang.Class<?>[] argsClasses,
                                                 @Nonnull
                                                 java.lang.Object[] args)
                                          throws java.lang.NoSuchMethodException
        Runs a method and returns the return value of that method If the method is a void method will return null
        Parameters:
        methodName - The method to invoke
        argsClasses - The classes of the arguments in the method in order.
        args - The actual arguments for the method in order.
        Returns:
        The output of the method or null if it is a void method
        Throws:
        java.lang.NoSuchMethodException - This exception is thrown when the given method name does not exist
        API Note
        I do not believe that you can use this method to run final methods because to my tests it does not work
